Subject: [PATCH 071/255] arm: mxc: fixup WDOG_WCR_REG undeclared error

This fix up below compiling error:
arch/arm/mach-imx/system.c:56:27: error: WDG_WCR_REG undeclared (first use in this function)
   iowrite16be(wcr_enable, WDOG_WCR_REG);

Signed-off-by: Jingchang Lu <jingchang.lu@freescale.com>
[Kevin: Original patch taken from
LS1021A-SDK-V1.1-ARM-SOURCE-20140815-yocto.iso]
Signed-off-by: Kevin Hao <kexin.hao@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm/mach-imx/system.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/mach-imx/system.c b/arch/arm/mach-imx/system.c
index 453fb3a..6e280a7 100644
--- a/arch/arm/mach-imx/system.c
+++ b/arch/arm/mach-imx/system.c
@@ -53,7 +53,7 @@ void mxc_restart(enum reboot_mode mode, const char *cmd)
 
 	/* Assert SRS signal */
 	if (big_endian)
-		iowrite16be(wcr_enable, WDOG_WCR_REG);
+		iowrite16be(wcr_enable, wdog_base);
 	else {
 		__raw_writew(wcr_enable, wdog_base);
 		/*
